The paper presents an algorithmic solution for detecting instances of a pattern with one variable in a given input string. This problem is related to string algorithms and data structures, which are covered in the cs.DS sub-category. The algorithm also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques, which are relevant to the cs.DM and cs.CC sub-categories. The use of a polynomially bounded integer alphabet suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and computational complexity (cs.SI) sub-categories.
